The fix introduces a boolean flag `checkServerIdentity` that is set to true by default. It ensures that the property `mail.smtp.ssl.checkserveridentity` is set to true unless the hostname verification policy is set to allow any host. This change enforces proper SSL hostname verification, thereby mitigating the risk of connecting to untrusted servers and enhancing the security of email transmission.

